The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Prime time in local animation 

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Hyderabad, Jan. 10: The animation industrys revenues are expected to grow three times to $869 million by 2010, Nasscom president Kiran Karnik said on Wednesday. 

 Animation and gaming has taken off in a big way in India in the past three years owing to the recognition of Indias IT expertise and creative skills, said Karnik while addressing an IT event in Hyderabad. 

 The annual report of Nasscom has projected a growth rate for the Indian animation industry at 25% and for gaming at 72 % over the next four years till 2010.The report said revenues for the animation industry were estimated at $354 million in 2006, a growth of 24 per cent over the previous year. 

 Karnik emphasised the need to set up an industry-support agency to standardise the processes and develop a standard curriculum for training institutes and trade promotion. 

 The animation and gaming industry also needs tax incentives and infrastructural support to attract investment, he said. 




